title: For Sale:  Concealed Weapons Permit Classes $75
postcontent:
The class is the NRA Basic Pistol / FL Concealed Weapons Permit class.  It covers safety, hands on classroom training, live fire training at the range, personal gun selection, cleaning/caring for a firearm and the laws/rules/procedures for the FL Concealed Weapons Permit. I also have a section of the class dedicated to personal defense with a firearm.  It is not necessary to own a firearm to attend the class as I have demo models.  If you own a firearm I recommend you bring it to class so you can train with it.  We typically spend 3 to 3 1/2 hours in the classroom and about an hour on the range. Once you complete the class you will receive a certificate that satisfies the requirements for the FL CWP.  You then fill out an application, have your fingerprints and picture taken and submit the application.  The cost of the actual permit is $70 and the fingerprint / back round check is $42.  The permit is good for 7 years.  I hold the public classes in the conference rooms at Homewood Suites by Pensacola Airport (or your location for a private class of 4 or more students).  The class is $75 per student and may be paid in cash, money order or local check.

This is a brand new in box Mossberg 930 Jerry Miculek Pro Series Tactical Class semi-automatic 12 gauge shotgun with a 3" chamber. In the world of competitive shooting, the name Jerry Miculek is synonymous with record-breaking success. A highly-accomplished shooter and five-time USPSA 3-Gun National Championship winner, Miculek depends on his equipment to reliably deliver when fractions of seconds count. Now you can shoot the same shotgun that this legendary champion uses. Mossberg proudly presents the Jerry Miculek Pro Series 930 Tactical Class of signature semi-automatic shotguns, built to Jerry Miculek's specifications. Special features include a 9 shot extended magazine tube, bevelled loading gate and shorter foreend for quick reloading, and an oversized bolt handle and release for easier operation. The receiver is laser engraved with "JM Pro-Series, Tactical Class."

Mossberg 930 shotguns feature a self-regulating gas system that vents excess gas to aid in recoil reduction and eliminate stress on critical components. All 930 autoloaders chamber both 2.75 inch and 3-inch 12-gauge shotshells with ease from target loads, to magnum loads, to the latest sabot slug ammo. The ambidextrous safety and included stock spacers ensure that this shotgun will fit any operator's requirements. The receiver features a drilled and tapped receiver for mounting optics, if desired. A high visibility fiber optic front sight is fitted.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Arisaka type 99 with Mum, Korean War bring back
postcontent: This is a Type 99 sporterized rifle that was brought back after the Korean War by my grandpa.  It has been in the basement for about 60 years and hasn't really been handled since it was brought back.  I recently found it and did a little cleaning with some Rem Oil wipes to get some surface grime off and checked to make sure it actually dry fired, which it does.  It is from the Toyo Kogyo Arsenal made between 1939-1945 and is a 34th series rifle, 7.7 cal.  The mum is still in great shape because it was a brought back personally by my grand father.  The rear trigger guard screw is missing but I plan to order a set from Numrich next week and install.  He believes he lost the screw shortly after bringing it back and stripping the rifle once.  The rifle has some slight rusting on the surface but nothing too serious it seems.  Shows to be a true war relic.  I can try to help provide any information possible. title: For Sale/Trade:  BEWARE OF ALPINE FIREARMS IN WOODLAND PARK, CO
location: Woodland Park, CO, Colorado Springs, Colorado
postcontent: DISHONEST GUN DEALER!!!  I travelled to this gun store with $2,000 cash in hand, excited to purchase a 1939 German Luger.  Jon Devaux, the owner, stated the pistol was numbers matching.  I asked him to disassemble the pistol so I could inspect the bore and confirm the serial numbers matched (to verify the $1,695 valuation of the pistol). Jon refused stating the only numbers I needed to see where on the barrel and outer receiver. I informed him that there were addition numbers on the components inside the pistol including under the trigger plate, the hold open bar, the bolt, extractor, firing pin, front toggle, and back toggle. The disassembly only takes about 30 seconds and does not require any tools. After I told Jon about the addition numbers he became defensive and said I could check AFTER I purchased the $1,695 pistol. This should be a red flag to any collector.  If he had nothing to hide he would have disassembled the pistol.  I have no doubt he is trying to sell a pistol that is NOT numbers matching for a numbers matching price. I WOULD NOT TRUST THIS DEALER.  MAKE THE DRIVE INTO COLORADO SPRINGS OR DENVER.
